    <h2><em>Puentes</em> Project</h2>
    <h3>Room for the integration of immigrants and their families.</h3>
    <div>
      The <em>Puentes</em> project wants to have a direct impact on the quality of life for newcomers to our society, who are in a position of vulnerability or risk of social exclusion, using multiculturalism as project basis.
    </div>
    <div>
      The origin of the idea of the <em>Puentes</em> Project emerges with the increase in immigration in recent times. For a newcomer, migration can become an opportunity for growth if you have the opportunity to use psychological and social resources to cope.
    </div>
    <h3>Project Definition: </h3>
    <div>
      It focuses on the psychological dimension of migration, covering family and interpersonal relations and relations with the hosting society.
    </div>
    <h3>Objectives: </h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Build bridges of communication, understanding and cooperation.</li>
      <li>Provide a place for support and interchange space to individuals and families who are in a migratory process.</li>
      <li>Increase the skills of individuals and families to handle the changes and effects of migration.</li>
    </ul>
