    <h2><em>Plenitud</em> Proyect</h2>
    <h3>Project on Systemic Social Coaching</h3>
    <div>
      The project will take action on situations or circumstances that may interfere with the establishment of satisfactory relationships and the achievement of well-being in relation to different areas of their lives, and from the willingness and commitment of these people. The project aims to implement an innovative methodology in the design of social work to be effective in the current social circumstances.
    </div>
    <div>
      This project, in this period of crisis and rupture of models, is necessary to help manage the discomfort of people through an innovative methodology for the ability to socialize and individualize responsibility. The current model of society often promotes the opposite: see the capacity as an individual skill, which is not shared. This project, based on systemic coaching tools, wants to work to make what is socially stimulating and integrating is common to everyone.
    </div>
    <div>
      The project is based on appreciative inquiry, in what we do well, to extract individual values ​​(set of attitudes, interests and orientations) that lead to a fulfilling life.
    </div>
    <div>
      The project has a network of coaches specialized in Systemic Coaching.
    </div>
