    <h2>Interversia Cycles</h2>
    <div>
      Babel Punto de Encuentro Foundation's Interversia Cycles are designed to improve the understanding of the environment and of ourselves in the context of migration processes through quality knowledge.
    </div>
    <div>
      Interversia are cycles of free talks aimed at people interested and involved in immigration whose main goal is to improve both the environment and knowledge of oneself and learn to use it as a nexus of interaction.
    </div>
    <div>
      Some of the topics covered in the lectures of Interversia are: recognize our perception of the society in which we live; learn to change the image that society has of ourselves; learn how to live in the city, by creating our own identity, through learning to participate in what the city has to offer and how to interact with it, or how to face the world of work, with its elements of discrimination and chances.
    </div>
    <div>
      The talks, which we like to call "Formative Dialogues", are the responsibility of the leading experts in their professional fields of study. Our goal is to create informal circles of interaction in which the basis of intercultural communication - understood as an exchange of knowledge - is to be done horizontally.
    </div>
    <div>
      At the end of the cycle, participants receive a diploma by the Fundación Babel Punto de Encuentro certifying their attendance.
    </div>
